 
    register_relay_channel()  ES II (28 Nov 1995)  register_relay_channel()
 
    NAME
        register_relay_channel -- register an object for receiving 
		channel message
 
    SYNOPSIS
        void register_relay_channel(string channel);
 
    DESCRIPTION
	by default, non-interactive objects will not be receiving channel
	messages at all, in order for it to receive channel messages, the
	object has to be registeered on the targeting channel's "listener
	list".

	register_relay_channel() puts the object that's calling this 
	function into the "listener list", where channel is the name of
	channel the object wishes to listen to.

	if the said channel does not exist, it will be ignored.

	this is used in conjunction with relay_channel().
 
    SEE ALSO
	relay_channel()
 
